ight, it stayed on. Also, we could not get it to turn off without unplugging it. On a busy morning, this could easily be the thing you forget to unplug. <a href=\"/best-curling-irons\">Curling iron</a> fires are not common, but there is still some risk, and there is always a burn risk too if someone assumes it is cool and puts their hand on it. A lot of older models lacked automatic shut-off, but since most of the units in our curling iron reviews have an automatic shut-off, this missing safety feature does stand out. It also lacks a stand so it just sort of rolls around on your countertop, which can be a fire or burn hazard. On the other hand, the <a href=\"http://staging.toptenreviews.com/health/wellness/best-curling-irons/remington-review/?status=InProgress\">Remington C191X</a> has all the safety features we looked for. ","The Arc Chi stands out for a few good reasons as well. It has a spring clip that is less than half the size of most. Also, the barrel rotates, which is unique. This makes it possible for the hair curler to do more of the work – you just clip the end of your hair in and push a button to have it roll the hair. You can push another button to have it unroll.","Some of our testers weren&#39;t crazy about the small clip or the automatic rolling feature, but it may just be a matter of getting used to it. The testers with short hair were the least impressed with the rolling feature, which makes sense since it is saving them less work. If you have long, thick hair it could be nice to have the hair rolling done for you.","Arc Chi has a huge temperature range so it works for all hair types and is one the best curling irons for long hair. It is generally the temperature it says it is, which is definitely not the case with many competitors. The display was digital and easy to read because of the blue backlighting. Most of the digital displays on competitors were hard to read.","This curling iron stands out with its red and gold design. One tester called it the Iron Man Curler. Appearance is not a reason to buy a curling iron, but it is a fun bonus on a unit like this that also makes long-lasting, shiny curls."]},"id":"93a2a523-eb32-4965-9613-4c1f2ac85e81","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"593eddb7-aa29-42a3-b1b8-fcd051b7dc7b","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Even with all of the design differences, most of our testers were happy with the curls the Chi Arc made, and they held up for hours in our timed tests. If you can get used to this curling iron it may well become your favorite. It heats up fast and has a huge temperature range that works well with all hair types. There are some safety concerns, but if you live in a house with adults and can remember to take a few precautions yourself you will enjoy this curling iron."]},"id":"f032fe1a-e881-4d96-9ab9-57bad3ade9b2","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_64410","url":"/farouk-chi-arc-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"angie-parkinson","url":"/author/angie-parkinson","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Angie Parkinson","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"4Pu3Dbh8P3CR8CNSJRVPZP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2015-04-27T15:48:27Z","datePublished":"2015-04-27T15:48:27Z","name":"Farouk Chi Arc","synopsis":"We have some safety concerns about the Farouk Arc Chi, but it did make great curls. One problem that we noticed was the lack of an automatic shutdown. Even when we left it on overnight, it stayed on.","review":{"rating":74,"verdict":"The smaller clip and mechanized rolling feature can be great once you get used to them, and the curl quality is wonderful.","pros":["This curling iron makes uniform, long-lasting curls."],"cons":["With no automatic shut-off or stand it has the potential to cause a fire."]},"strapline":"We have some safety concerns about the Farouk Arc Chi, but it did make great curls. One problem that we noticed was the la